  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Col Alto is one of our favourite hotels in the <a data-udi="umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393" href="/{localLink:umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393}" title="The Dolomites Ski Area">Dolomites</a>. There’s plenty going on in the village and you can walk to bars, shops and restaurants. It might be hard to tear yourself away from the hotel though. We love its modern alpine style.</p>
<h2>Hotel shuttle</h2>
<p>The location couldn’t be better in central <a data-udi="umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8}" title="Corvara &amp; Colfosco">Corvara</a> and just 400 metres from the Boe gondola. It's the best place if you want to head straight out and get onto the brilliant Sellaronda circuit.</p>
<p>If you don't fancy carrying your skis, the hotel runs a shuttle to and from the slopes every morning and afternoon.</p>
<h2>Lounge &amp; bar</h2>
<p>The Iceberg Lounge Bar is the perfect place to grab a drink and catch up with friends before or after dinner - be sure to try one of the creative cocktails on offer. After a day of snowy adventures, the bar is also the perfect place to enjoy a warming hot chocolate in front of the fireplace. </p>
<p>The food at the hotel is also delicious. Expect traditional South Tyrolean dishes with a modern twist. They go to great lengths to make sure the ingredients used are local so everything tastes fresh and authentic.</p>
<h2>Indoor pool</h2>
<p>When it comes to relaxing, the Col Alto has you covered. The wellness centre is the perfect space to spend a few hours relaxing, enjoy a dip in the indoor pool with waterfall, soothe any aches in the whirlpool, or choose from the five saunas and steam baths for ultimate relaxation. When the sun is out, there is no better place to put your feet up and relax than the solarium, with comfortable loungers and large windows with mountain views - it is a great spot after a busy day exploring the Dolomites. If you want to completely unwind, why not book a massage or treatment for a little extra fee.</p>
<h3>Why is this an Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Central location</strong> - With an excellent location in the centre of Corvara and a hotel shuttle to the lifts, you couldn't be better placed to explore the Dolomites.</p>
<p><strong>Food &amp; drink</strong> - You will find locally sourced dishes at the Hotel Col Alto which showcase some of the best product from the Southern Tyrol region.</p>
<p><strong>Wellness area</strong><span> - There is nowhere better to be than relaxing in the wellness facilities after a day on the slopes including an indoor pool with waterfall, whirlpool and multiple saunas.</span></p>]]></description>
