  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Twin Rooms </strong>sleep two people and are 22m². They have a bath or shower.</p>
<p><strong>Twin Classic Rooms</strong> are 30-36m² and can sleep up to three using a French sofa bed. They have a bath and lounge/seating area.</p>
<p><strong>Superior </strong><strong>Twin Rooms </strong>are 30-36m², sleep two to four people (extra bed is a French sofa bed) and have a shower.</p>
<p><strong>Martagon </strong><strong>Double or Twin Rooms </strong>sleep two to four people (extra bed is a French sofa bed and suitable for children only). They're between 30-36m² and have a lounge/seating area, bath and shower. These rooms are in the hotel's annex building and cannot be adjacent to any other room types. An underground tunnel connects the two buildings.</p>
<p><strong>Sassongher </strong><strong>Suites </strong>are 45m² so have loads of space. They sleep up to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed) and have views of the Sassongher mountain. They also have a lounge/seating area, bath and shower.  </p>
<p><strong>Double Rooms for single use </strong>are 22m² and have a shower.</p>
<p><strong>Bedroom Facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Balcony</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Mini-fridge</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
